channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Prosecutors question Michael Cohen in Trump hush money trial
item.description: Donald Trump's ex-attorney Michael Cohen continues to testify Monday in the former president's criminal hush money trial in New York. Follow here for the latest live news updates, analysis and more.

item.title: Investigators return to Long Island home of Gilgo Beach serial killing suspect
item.description: Police vehicles were seen outside Rex Heuermann's single-family home.

item.title: Iran's President Raisi killed in helicopter crash
item.description: Iran's President Ebrahim Raisi has died in a helicopter crash, the government has confirmed. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Hunter Biden presses for delay in federal gun trial
item.description: Hunter Biden asked an appeals court to pause the trial, set to begin next month.

item.title: Israel-Hamas war: War crimes warrants sought for Sinwar and Netanyahu
item.description: Israeli war cabinet divisions broke into the open over the weekend when member Benny Gantz demanded the cabinet lay out a plan for the war against Hamas by June 8, threatening to otherwise withdraw from the government. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Trump trial live updates: Michael Cohen explains why he took extra $30K
item.description: Follow the latest developments in former President Donald Trump's criminal hush money trial in New York.

item.title: May 19, 2024 helicopter crash involving Iranian president
item.description: A helicopter carrying Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi crashed while he was visiting a northern region in the country Sunday, according to the Iranian state news agency IRNA.

item.title: Mayor defends NYPD response after officers seen punching pro-Palestinian protesters
item.description: New York City Mayor Eric Adams defended the police department’s response to a pro-Palestinian street demonstration in Brooklyn over the weekend, calling video of officers repeatedly punching men lying prone on the ground an “isolated incident.”

item.title: May 19, 2024 - Israel-Gaza news
item.description: An Israeli airstrike on a refugee camp in central Gaza has killed at least 35 people, including seven children, according to hospital officials. Meanwhile, Israeli war cabinet divisions are spilling into the open.

item.title: Judge rules Ohio law that keeps cities from banning flavored tobacco is unconstitutional
item.description: Ohio law that keeps cities from banning flavored tobacco ruled unconstitutional.
